method.name: is_nil
method.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if iterator points to nil, [code]false[/code] if not [b]Complexity:[/b] [i]O(1)[/i]

method.name: next
method.description: The iterator points to the smallest key greater than the current key, if there is no bigger key, it points to nil. Returns itself. [b]Complexity:[/b] [i]O(logN)[/i]

method.name: prev
method.description: The iterator points to the biggest key smaller than the current key, if there is no smaller key, it points to nil. Returns itself. [b]Complexity:[/b] [i]O(logN)[/i]

method.name: get_value
method.description: Returns the key value the iterator is pointing. [b]Complexity:[/b] [i]O(1)[/i]
